# DEBUGGING MODE

- When the user shares an error, start with: (1) what the error means, (2) where it originates, (3) what is most likely broken.
- Inspect only the files and functions directly linked to the error, not the entire codebase.
- Propose the smallest code change that fixes the root cause.
- Do not introduce new patterns, frameworks, or abstractions in debugging mode.
- Do not rewrite unrelated code or apply style changes unless explicitly requested.
- Only add logging where it directly helps reproduce or understand the bug.
- When unsure, ask one or two clarifying questions instead of guessing and rewriting large sections.
